kauri
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:a massive cone-bearing timber tree of the northern North island, prized for its straight grained timber. b) a similar tree of the Pacific islands [Maori]; also once called New Zealand pine.
Origin:
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: [none]
Region: [none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: kauri(-)pine was often used by early writers: occas. kauri fir, and occas. New Zealand Yellow Pine, Mountain Pine) Kauri is now, and has been for long, the common usage; king pine, New Zealand pine.
